Sentencas: Using a large-scale, experimentally captured 3D microstructure data set, we implement the generative adversarial network (GAN) framework to learn and generate 3D microstructures of solid oxide fuel cell electrodes.
Titulo: Microstructure Generation via Generative Adversarial Network for Heterogeneous, Topologically Complex 3D Materials

Sentencas: The generated microstructures are visually, statistically, and topologically realistic, with distributions of microstructural parameters, including volume fraction, particle size, surface area, tortuosity, and triple-phase boundary density, being highly similar to those of the original microstructure.
Titulo: Microstructure Generation via Generative Adversarial Network for Heterogeneous, Topologically Complex 3D Materials

Sentencas: These results are compared and contrasted with those from an established, grain-based generation algorithm (DREAM.3D).
Titulo: Microstructure Generation via Generative Adversarial Network for Heterogeneous, Topologically Complex 3D Materials

Sentencas: Importantly, simulations of electrochemical performance, using a locally resolved finite element model, demonstrate that the GAN-generated microstructures closely match the performance distribution of the original, while DREAM.3D leads to significant differences.
Titulo: Microstructure Generation via Generative Adversarial Network for Heterogeneous, Topologically Complex 3D Materials

Sentencas: The ability of the generative machine learning model to recreate microstructures with high fidelity suggests that the essence of complex microstructures may be captured and represented in a compact and manipulatable form.
Titulo: Microstructure Generation via Generative Adversarial Network for Heterogeneous, Topologically Complex 3D Materials
